Preheat oven to 350Â°F. Roast sweet potatoes on a rimmed baking sheet until tender, about 1 hour. Let cool slightly. Remove skins and transfer sweet potatoes to a large heavy saucepan over low heat. Add cream cheese and butter. Mash until well blended and creamy. Season with salt and pepper. Stir over low heat until hot. Spoon into a warm serving dish and garnish with cheese and pecans.